We recommended that the Municipal Mayor and the Human Resource Management Officer ensure that travel allowances are paid only to JO personnel whose contracts explicitly authorize travel;

We also recommended that the Municipal Mayor issue an Executive Order establishing clear internal policies, guidelines, and limitations on travel claims for JO personnel; and


Furthermore, we recommended that the Municipal Accountant thoroughly review the travel claims of JO personnel to ensure they are properly approved by the authorized official and supported by the required certifications and other necessary documents before processing payment.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the Municipal Treasurer to:
Stop the practice of encashing private checks using local collections;
Deposit all collections intact and daily in accordance with the above-mentioned regulation;
Instruct all collecting officers to remit all their collections daily for deposit and to prepare the Report of Collections and Deposits on daily basis;
Make sure that collecting officers are not issued additional accountable forms (AF) unless collections from previously issued AF are remitted intact; 

Stop designating as collectors, those who habitually disregard the mentioned rules, laws and regulations; and


Perform diligently his duties and responsibilities as the Municipal Treasurer.

