We recommended the Management to:
Require that reconciliation between the records of the MA and GSO be undertaken and effect the necessary adjustments in the accounting books to fairly present the said accounts in the financial statements;
Perform One-Time Cleansing of PPE as prescribed in COA Circular 2020-006 to be able to establish PPE balances that are verifiable as to existence, condition, and accountability;
Require the GSO to prepare and maintain Property Cards for all PPE accounts;
Dispose of the unserviceable properties and the corresponding cost or value be dropped from the books of accounts; and
Require the Municipal Accountant to ensure that all ongoing projects are recorded under the CIP account, and subsequently transferred to its corresponding PPE account upon completion of the project for a fair presentation of the financial statements.

We reiterated our previous year’s recommendation that Management require the Municipal Accountant to:
Trace the transactions and prepare/maintain subsidiary ledgers indicating details of transactions such as the name of specific projects, receipts, disbursements, or any adjustments for the total balance of ₱1,137,772.20 as of December 31, 2023, otherwise, provide adequate disclosure in the notes to financial statements; and ensure that a separate subsidiary record/ledger is maintained for each succeeding account/project;
Properly maintain the Subsidiary Ledgers for all fund transfers to support their respective control accounts and utilize available records to obtain details of the balances and prepare the adjusting entries to ensure the accuracy and validity of the balances presented in the financial statements;
Liquidate fund transfers once projects are fully implemented and/or refund the unutilized amount from completed projects and require the appropriate recording in the books of accounts; and
Transfer the amount of ₱ 3,510,102.13 as of December 31, 2023 under the General Fund to the Trust Fund.
In addition, it is recommended that the concerned Implementing Offices always furnish the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer with a copy of the MOA for every program/project to serve as the guidelines in the disbursement of the funds and provide all the information needed in the recording of the same.

